body:
So, I finally jumped on the bandwagon™️ and created a Rymesona for myself! My Pokémon partners would be Bulbasaur, Skiddo, Phantump, and Mudbray. I certainly could not choose just one.

  • I would work as a florist on the outskirts of Ryme City & also sell produce at my shop that I grow from my garden at home.
  • Mudbray would often wear saddlebags to help me carry items & transport my wares. He would also pull a wagon to sometimes transport my other poke-partners— he’s a great help!
  • Mudbray’s saddlebags would often contain: spray bottle of water (plant types obvs), my planner & pen, instant film camera, and snacks.
  • Phantump would be very anxious around the bustling city, therefore, would need to be in a baby carrier strapped to me a lot of the time.
  • Skiddo & Bulbasaur would love helping in the shop & garden at home, and would probably be better than me at gardening.
  • Skiddo & Bulbasaur would love playing with Phantump, & often make Mudbray join the fun too.
  • We would all live inside our cottage home, there is plenty of room & some to spare.

(It’s not great, and it’s very rushed, but I wanted to join the fun.) (Click image for higher quality.)

title: ¿Garbodor en Detective Pikachu? ¡Un nuevo arte conceptual de la pelea contra Charizard apunta a ello!
body:
¿Garbodor en Detective Pikachu? ¡Un nuevo arte conceptual de la pelea contra Charizard apunta a ello!

Si hablamos de la incursión de los monstruos de bolsillo en el mundo del cine, entonces no podemos dejar de lado Detective Pikachu, la cual ha sido la primera película de acción real en la que hemos podido ver cómo estas criaturas fantásticas se adaptan a un universomás real. Durante el desarrollo de cualquier producto surgen muchas ideas, y algunas de ellas acaban desechándose, como ha ocurrido…
